der=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"width:1200px;\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td>Crush Orange<br>\n\t\t\tSoft drink<br>\n\t\t\t12-pack, 12&nbsp;fl. oz. per can<\/td>\n\t\t\t<td>Bubly Orange<br>\n\t\t\tSparkling water<br>\n\t\t\t12-pack, 12 fl. oz. per can<\/td>\n\t\t<\/tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td><img height=\"450\" src=\"https:\/\/nyu.qualtrics.com\/CP\/Graphic.php?IM=IM_cUPEQpIIBFMyfQ1\" style=\"width: 749px; height: 450px;\" width=\"749\"><\/td>\n\t\t\t<td><img height=\"450\" src=\"https:\/\/nyu.qualtrics.com\/CP\/Graphic.php?IM=IM_3gWQGCf66lXZkEZ\" style=\"width: 288px; height: 450px;\" width=\"288\"><\/td>\n\t\t<\/tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td>Click <a href=\"https:\/\/drive.google.com\/file\/d\/163JG14YnW2_FfcSghIt_BhF1YbqAx-PM\/view?usp=sharing\" id=\"crush_g\" target=\"_blank\">here<\/a> to see nutrition facts.<\/td>\n\t\t\t<td>Click <a href=\"https:\/\/drive.google.com\/file\/d\/1DRxZz7HqXYlMMW6fwkJ5f04pdiAgozVH\/view?usp=sharing\" id=\"crush_g_2\" target=\"_blank\">here<\/a> to see nutrition facts.<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/div>","DataExportTag":"Q938","QuestionID":"QID938"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9Xle3s32xKQvH2C","Element":"QG","PrimaryAttribute":"QG_PoeNpIt0QEAv6cN","SecondaryAttribute":"Default Quota Group","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"ID":"QG_PoeNpIt0QEAv6cN","Name":"Default Quota Group","Selected":true,"MultipleMatch":"PlaceInAll","Public":false,"Quotas":["QO_WiCMxJc6AQQvdd9"]}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9Xle3s32xKQvH2C","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID740","SecondaryAttribute":"How many calories do you think are in one 12-ounce serving of the following types of drinks? A no...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">How many <strong>calories <\/strong>do you think are in one 12-ounce serving of the following types of drinks?<\/span><\/span>\n<ul>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">A normal can of soda is 12 ounces. For reference, the official U.S. &ldquo;Nutrition Facts&rdquo; labels consider a benchmark intake of 2,000 calories for one person in a day.<\/span><\/span><\/li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">We don&rsquo;t want you to look up the official answer, just give us your best guess based on what you currently know.<\/span><\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"calories_description","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"How many calories do you think are in one 12-ounce serving of the following types of drinks? A no...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID740"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9Xle3s32xKQvH2C","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID747","SecondaryAttribute":"How many grams of sugar do you think are contained in one 12-ounce serving of the following types...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">How many <strong>grams of sugar<\/strong> do you think are contained in one 12-ounce serving of the following types of drinks?<\/span><\/span>\n<ul>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">A normal can of soda is 12 ounces. For reference, nutritional guidelines often consider a benchmark intake of about 30 grams of added sugars for one person in a day.<\/span><\/span><\/li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">We don&rsquo;t want you to look up the official answer, just give us your best guess based on what you currently know.<\/span><\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"How many grams of sugar do you think are contained in one 12-ounce serving of the following types...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">How many calories do you think are in one 12-ounce serving of the following types of drinks? (A normal can of soda is 12 ounces. For reference, the official U.S. &ldquo;Nutrition Facts&rdquo; labels consider a benchmark intake of 2,000 calories for one person in a day.) We don&rsquo;t want you to look up the official answer, just give us your best guess based on what you currently know.<\/span><\/span>","DataExportTag":"sugar description","QuestionID":"QID747"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9Xle3s32xKQvH2C","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID776","SecondaryAttribute":"Imagine the computer selects you to receive the 12 pack of Coca-Cola. We'd like to know how you w...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Imagine the computer selects you to receive the 12 pack of Coca-Cola. We'd like to know how you would (hypothetically) trade off earning additional payments vs. receiving drink containers with the label.<\/span><\/div>\n\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\"><br>\n<img src=\"https:\/\/microsoft.qualtrics.com\/CP\/Graphic.php?IM=IM_4UheVwFZcpZd3WS\" style=\"width: 350px; height: 123px;\"><br><br><\/div>\n\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Please choose the option you prefer (left or right) <b>in each row<\/b>. The option on the right gets